        <section id="about">
            <h2>About Site Security</h2>
            <p>
                Welcome to the Security Department of our private Roblox SCP Roleplay server. 
                The Security Department is responsible for the safety of all personnel and the containment of SCPs. 
                Our primary role is to respond to threats, enforce site protocols, and maintain order within the facility.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section id="roles">
            <h2>Security Roles</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Security Cadet:</strong> New recruits in basic training, learning site protocols and basic defense.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Security Officer:</strong> Patrolling the facility, responding to incidents, and assisting higher-ranking staff.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Security Sergeant:</strong> Leading teams during breaches or drills, managing lower-ranking personnel.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Security Chief:</strong> Overseeing department operations, organizing response teams, and liaising with other departments.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="protocols">
            <h2>Site Protocols</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Always carry your ID and follow instructions from higher-ranking staff.</li>
                <li>Report suspicious activity or breaches immediately.</li>
                <li>Non-essential personnel must stay clear of containment zones during incidents.</li>
                <li>Use non-lethal force unless authorized otherwise.</li>
                <li>Maintain communication with your team at all times.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section id="contact">
            <h2>Contact & Join Us</h2>
            <p>
                Interested in joining the Security Department? Contact the server admin on Roblox (user: <strong>Toxicbooking</strong>)
                or join our private Discord server for applications and more info.
            </p>
